        <div class="Gameplay__grid--one text">
          <h4>1) Take</h4>
          <p>The game works by players successively taking a brick out, without nocking the stack over.</p>
          <p>Players can use only one hand and cannot hold the stack, the player that crashes it loses all their points.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="Gameplay__grid--two text">
          <h4>2) Answer</h4>
          <p>Each brick, called <%= brick_prefix %> <%= brick_single %>, has two prompts written on it corresponding to a difficulty scale and level of intimacy intended to be invoked.</p>
          <p>The player picks a prompt, in one game mode the player answers the prompt themselves, in another you ask the next person and they respond.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="Gameplay__grid--two image">
          <img src="/img/instructions-two.png" alt="Game instructions two, image of someone holding <%= brick_prefix %> <%= brick_single %> to considder it's prompt">
        </div>
        <div class="Gameplay__grid--three image">
          <img src="/img/instructions-three.png" alt="Game instructions three, image of someone placing the <%= brick_single %> bcak on the stack">
        </div>
        <div class="Gameplay__grid--three text">
          <h4>3) Build</h4>
          <p>On successful answering of the question (judged by the consensus of the other players), the person receives in game currency, called ‘Squids’, corresponding with the colour / difficulty.</p>
          <p>If the player does not answer, they get no points and the round moves on. The player who pulled the brick must place it back on top, building a gradually more unstable stack until the game is over.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
